# No new duplicate types

**Rule:** Before adding a new `*Position*`, `*Order*`, `*Account*`, or `*Metrics*` struct, check whether an existing type can be reused. If a new type is needed, add at least one `From` conversion to or from an existing canonical type. Avoid orphaned duplicates.

## Canonical examples (non-exhaustive)

| Type | Location | Role |
|------|----------|------|
| `broker_engine::domain::Position` | `broker_engine/src/domain.rs` | Broker-agnostic position |
| `common::PositionSnapshot` | `common/src/snapshot.rs` | NATS / proto snapshot |
| `api::IbPositionDto`, `RuntimePositionDto`, … | `api/src/` | REST / runtime views |
| `broker_engine::domain::AccountInfo` | `broker_engine/src/domain.rs` | Raw account |
| `common::Metrics` | `common/src/snapshot.rs` | Snapshot metrics |

## Adding a new snapshot-shaped type

1. Prefer extending `common` types used by 2+ crates.
2. If a new struct is required, place it in `crates/common/` when shared across `api` / `nats_adapter` / others (see `AGENTS.md` shared-types pattern).
3. Add `From<…>` in both directions where conversions exist.
4. Explain in the commit why a new type was necessary.

## Quick checks

```bash
rg "pub struct.*Position" agents/backend/crates --type rust
rg "pub struct.*Account|pub struct.*Metrics" agents/backend/crates --type rust
```

**Parity:** Same policy as `.opencode/rules/no-new-duplicate-types.md` (OpenCode). **Also see** `AGENTS.md` (shared types + `derive_builder` patterns) and `.opencode/rules/shared-types-pattern.md`.
